         <component>
            <section ID="LINK_20e8e1b3-2ff9-4a9e-b354-1cf33175fcfe">
               <id root="20e8e1b3-2ff9-4a9e-b354-1cf33175fcfe"/>
               <code code="34088-5" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="OVERDOSAGE SECTION"/>
               <title>OVERDOSAGE</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>Topically applied corticosteroids can be absorbed in sufficient amounts to produce systemic effects (see <content styleCode="bold">
                        <linkHtml href="#LINK_e58fca51-f046-4c96-80e7-33c5198fd7e3">PRECAUTIONS</linkHtml>
                     </content>).</paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20120201"/>
            </section>
         </component>
         <component>
            <section ID="LINK_ed61281e-8801-40e6-be1b-047f16d26c4c">
               <id root="ed61281e-8801-40e6-be1b-047f16d26c4c"/>
               <code code="34068-7" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="DOSAGE &amp; ADMINISTRATION SECTION"/>
               <title>DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>Topical corticosteroids are generally applied to the affected area as a thin film from two to four times daily depending on the severity of the condition.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Occlusive dressings may be used for the management of psoriasis or recalcitrant conditions.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>If an infection develops, the use of occlusive dressings should be discontinued and appropriate antimicrobial therapy instituted.</paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20120201"/>
            </section>
         </component>
